---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Ryuteki Kitchen | Designing a Modern Classic Dining Journey"
  description="A bilingual case study for Ryuteki Kitchen, a luxury Chinese restaurant that merges heritage cuisine with a contemporary atmosphere. Immersive visuals and streamlined reservations boosted young customer engagement."
  alternateHref="/"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">CASE STUDY</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Designing a Modern Classic Dining Journey</h1>
      <p class="hero-description">
        We united generations of refined Chinese cuisine with a modern spatial narrative. Sensory storytelling and a rebuilt reservation flow invite guests to taste the aroma and energy of Ryuteki Kitchen before they arrive.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="cta-button" href="#reservation">Reserve Online</a>
        <a class="secondary-cta" href="#concept">View Design Concept</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="placeholder-frame" role="img" aria-label="Placeholder visuals for dishes and interior">
      <span class="placeholder-label">Visual Placeholder</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="experience">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Experience Strategy</p>
      <h2>Rebuilding Reservations & Brand Immersion</h2>
      <p>
        Interviews, journey mapping, and competitor research shaped a storyline that keeps anticipation high from discovery to booking. Category-based galleries and time-specific CTAs were orchestrated to convert curiosity into reservations.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="comparison">
        <div class="comparison-column">
          <h3 class="card-title">Before</h3>
          <p>
            The previous site was information-heavy yet visually flat with phone-only bookings. The lack of exclusivity messaging failed to attract guests in their 20s and 30s.
          </p>
          <div class="placeholder-frame" role="img" aria-label="Legacy website placeholder">
            <span class="placeholder-label">Before Placeholder</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison-column">
          <h3 class="card-title">After</h3>
          <p>
            Courses now unfold through immersive imagery with persistent reservation access. The new flow magnifies aroma, texture, and sound to drive a 1.5x lift in bookings.
          </p>
          <div class="placeholder-frame" role="img" aria-label="New website placeholder">
            <span class="placeholder-label">After Placeholder</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Scope</h3>
          <p>Site redesign / Photo direction / Reservation UX</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Impact</h3>
          <p>1.5× web reservations / Higher share of guests aged 20–30</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Timeline</h3>
          <p>8 weeks from discovery to launch</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="concept">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Design Concept</p>
      <h2>Capturing the Moment a Dragon Takes Flight</h2>
      <p>
        Crimson gradients meet inky depth and gleaming gold, evoking the rising steam and sizzling energy of signature dishes. UI modules channel the glow of lacquered interiors while preserving breathing space for dramatic imagery.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Amplified Sizzle</h3>
          <p>
            A course-driven scroll reveals dishes in sequence, framed for future steam fades and spice particle animations. Every module was planned with motion markers to minimize development friction.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Lustrous Interface</h3>
          <p>
            Metallic gleams and shadowed gradients mirror the evening ambience. The global nav transitions from translucent to solid while scrolling, striking a balance between immersion and clarity.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="card-title">Color Story</h3>
        <div class="color-swatches">
          <div class="color-chip">
            <span style="background:#7F1D1D;color:#f8fafc;">Crimson #7F1D1D</span>
            <span class="tone">Core heat & intensity</span>
          </div>
          <div class="color-chip">
            <span style="background:#0F172A;color:#f8fafc;">Ink #0F172A</span>
            <span class="tone">Poised stillness</span>
          </div>
          <div class="color-chip">
            <span style="background:#FACC15;color:#0f172a;">Gold #FACC15</span>
            <span class="tone">Luxurious accents</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Typography</h3>
          <p>
            Headlines lean on bold Mincho characters, contrasted with a modern sans for English copy. Vertical dish names add authenticity while spacing preserves bilingual legibility.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Interaction Plan</h3>
          <p>
            Steam-like hover fades and spice particles on scroll are mapped for a future release. Prototype markers identify rhythm and duration, keeping the experience cohesive across devices.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="storytelling">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Visual Storytelling</p>
      <h2>Inviting Guests to Savor the Course Narrative</h2>
      <p>
        Seasonal tasting menus, dim sum, mains, and desserts rise through a staggered gallery that mimics plating cadence. Alternating dining scenes and architectural shots communicate the five-senses journey.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Course Gallery</h3>
          <p>
            Scroll-triggered reveals elevate each course, priming guests for the next flavor. Placeholder frames mark future photo sets and cinemagraph slots.
          </p>
          <div class="placeholder-frame" role="img" aria-label="Course gallery placeholder">
            <span class="placeholder-label">Course Gallery Placeholder</span>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Detail-First Layout</h3>
          <p>
            Macro cuts spotlight steam, glaze, and spice textures. Layout guides ensure every close-up swap keeps intensity, even before final photography is delivered.
          </p>
          <div class="placeholder-frame" role="img" aria-label="Detail photography placeholder">
            <span class="placeholder-label">Detail Cut Placeholder</span>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      <article class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title">Responsive System</h3>
        <p>
          Mobile devices gain a full-screen carousel that alternates video and stills. Desktop users can compare course compositions at a glance with adaptive table layouts.
        </p>
        <p>
          Multilingual readiness is baked in with vertical rubi spacing, balanced line heights, and resilient grids for longer English descriptions.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="results">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Results</p>
      <h2>Boosting Young Guest Reservations Through UX</h2>
      <p>
        Micro conversions punctuate the page to capture intent peaks. Sensory narratives link directly to booking modules, guiding guests from appetite to action seamlessly.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="stat-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-value">+52%</p>
          <p class="stat-caption">Increase in online reservations</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-value">1.5×</p>
          <p class="stat-caption">More guests aged 20–30</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-value">-38%</p>
          <p class="stat-caption">Drop in checkout abandonment</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-value">2.2×</p>
          <p class="stat-caption">Growth in review submissions</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <article class="quote">
        <p>
          “The photography plan captures aroma so vividly that guests comment on it. WeChat inquiries feel effortless now, and we see clear growth in younger Japanese diners.”
        </p>
        <cite>Owner Li, Ryuteki Kitchen</cite>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="flow">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Process</p>
      <h2>Four Phases to Relaunch the Brand in Eight Weeks</h2>
      <p>
        A tightly orchestrated workflow ensured vision coherence from research to post-launch optimization, keeping every stakeholder aligned.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="process-steps">
        <article class="process-step">
          <h3 class="card-title">01 Research & Journey Design</h3>
          <p>Guest interviews, competitive reviews, and shot planning defined expectations for sensory storytelling and booking UX.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="process-step">
          <h3 class="card-title">02 Visual Concept Development</h3>
          <p>We set tone, camera angles, and motion beats while prototyping micro-animation cues that echo rising steam.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="process-step">
          <h3 class="card-title">03 Design & Implementation</h3>
          <p>UI components absorbed new imagery in parallel with building A/B-ready call-to-action variants and integrated forms.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="process-step">
          <h3 class="card-title">04 Launch & Operations</h3>
          <p>SEO/MEO targeting, review flows, and editorial calendars were prepared to sustain momentum after go-live.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="reservation">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Reservation UX</p>
      <h2>Layered Calls to Action That Match Guest Intent</h2>
      <p>
        Lunch, dinner, and private-room CTAs adapt their tone and color. Guests can select party size, course, and allergy notes within a single screen, then jump to reviews for reassurance.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <article class="reservation-panel">
        <h3 class="card-title">Instant Booking Form (Coming Soon)</h3>
        <p>
          Imagery, guest reviews, and seating recommendations live together to keep momentum. Post-submission flows invite loyalty sign-ups and repeat visits.
        </p>
        <div class="reservation-actions">
          <a class="cta-button" href="https://example.com/reserve" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Book Online</a>
          <a class="cta-button secondary" href="tel:+81300000000">Call Us</a>
          <a class="cta-button secondary" href="https://example.com/wechat" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">WeChat</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Time-Specific CTAs</h3>
          <p>Dynamic microcopy and colorways mirror guest intent peaks, reinforcing exclusivity while staying actionable.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Mobile Persistent CTA</h3>
          <p>A bottom-fixed button keeps booking a tap away for travelers browsing on smartphones, particularly important for overseas guests.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
